{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013epmCaJQ2e5JcXBnJNNGuT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze each failure and propose specific fixes.\n\n**Failure 1: Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander → ''**\n- Root cause: Mixed-case 2-line title join gets destroyed by \"shorter wins\" dedup\n- The single line \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" is a substring of the join, so the join is removed\n- Then the partial line alone may not pass threshold\n\n**Failure 2: FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS → FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS**\n\n\n- Root cause: Structural bonus on first title inflates bestBaseScore, second title without structural bonus falls below threshold\n\n**Failure 3: SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D) → FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)**\n- Root cause: Garbled OCR fragment passes isStructuralHeading, hijacks structural heading role, inflates threshold\n\nThe key fix is reversing the dedup logic to favor multi-line joins over their component lines — when a candidate is a 2-line join and a shorter candidate is a substring, I should keep the join instead.  But I need to handle ingredient run-ons carefully, where the extra part contains measurements and should be stripped. I'll tag candidates during buildCandidates with an `isJoin` flag, then during dedup prefer the join only when the shorter candidate is actually one of its component lines, otherwise keep the existing behavior.\n\nFor the threshold, I should exclude the structural bonus from the bestBaseScore calculation so it helps the first heading win without raising the bar for other candidates. And for detecting garbled OCR in structural headings, I can check if the first significant word looks like plausible English or Polish — either requiring it to be at least 5 characters or validating it against a noise embedding before awarding the structural bonus.\n\nThe simplest fix is to compute embeddings first, then only award the structural bonus if the rawScore is positive, which means the candidate actually matches the title semantically. For mixed-case titles that don't meet the floor threshold, I could add a scoring boost for candidates that look like proper titles with multiple words in title case.\n\nOn the dedup side, the core issue is that the current logic always prefers shorter candidates, but that breaks when the longer one is a join that adds non-ingredient text. I need to tag candidates as joins and then check whether the extra content looks like ingredient quantities or continuation text—if it's continuation, prefer the join instead.\n\nBut there's a guard comment in the code warning against changing this logic, so modifying dedup directly feels risky. A safer approach might be to handle this upstream during candidate generation: mark which candidates come from joins, then during dedup, skip the \"shorter wins\" rule when comparing a join to its component lines, unless the join itself contains ingredient patterns.\n\nActually, I think the cleanest solution is to add a pre-dedup filtering step that mirrors the existing structural heading prefix removal. Before dedup runs, I'll identify any 2-line joins whose component single-lines are also candidates, and if the join doesn't contain measurement patterns, remove those component lines so dedup can't eliminate the join. Then I'll also adjust how the structural bonus factors into threshold calculations—using just the raw score plus all-caps bonus, excluding the structural bonus from that threshold computation.\n\nFor the structural bonus itself, I should validate it with embedding scores: only apply it if the candidate's raw score is above zero, which filters out garbled OCR fragments that shouldn't get the bonus in the first place. And if there are no all-caps candidates at all, I might need to add a title-case bonus or lower the floor threshold slightly for mixed-case candidates that follow proper title patterns.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":222,"cache_read_input_tokens":29023,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":222},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e3944d0-338c-40b1-a9ee-b5ee0be23ae4","uuid":"bb760dbc-0ad2-4b87-852e-bcc69f60ea5f"}
