{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HUDoRxYZ9ZeeBa9QBwpSev","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me outline my thinking on each failure before writing the plan.\n\n**Failure 1 (Baked Eggs → ''):** The 2-line join is the correct answer, but \"shorter wins\" dedup kills it because the single first line is a substring. The fix from iteration 4's plan (protect continuation joins where the second part starts with `&`/`/`/`+`/`:`) was proposed but never implemented — `buildCandidates` still lacks origin tracking. I'll re-propose this with clearer implementation details.\n\n**Failure 2 (Finnish Flatbreads → only first):** `structuralBonus` (+0.10) is exclusive to `firstStructuralHeading`, inflating `bestBaseScore` so the second title falls below threshold. Two options: distribute the bonus across all structural headings, or exclude `structuralBonus` from the threshold computation. I'll propose excluding it from threshold — it's a simpler, more surgical fix.\n\n**Failure 3 (Saffron → garbled OCR):** The garbled `FRON WHEAT BUNS` wins `baseHeading` by position alone. The fix is to defer structural heading selection until after embeddings, picking by `rawScore` quality instead of document order. Plus the continuation join protection from Fix 1 solves the secondary dedup issue.\n\nNow let me write the detailed plan."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4550,"cache_read_input_tokens":31109,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4550},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e3944d0-338c-40b1-a9ee-b5ee0be23ae4","uuid":"753f531c-ef15-4e05-82a3-ec24f73056fb"}
